sor Generics","text":"","code":"pak::pak(\"r-xla/tengen\")"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/index.html","id":"available-generics","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Available Generics","title":"Tensor Generics","text":"shape(): Different dim() also supporting 0-dimensional tensors. dtype(): Returns data type tensor. as_array(): Converts tensor R array. as_raw(): Converts tensor raw() vector. device(): Returns device tensor. functions: ndims(): Returns number dimensions tensor. implemented length(shape(x)). nelts(): Returns number elements tensor. implemented prod(shape(x)).","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/index.html","id":"tensor-data-types","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Tensor Data Types","title":"Tensor Generics","text":"tengen provides S3 class hierarchy representing tensor data types via DataType: BooleanType() - Boolean (i1 / pred / bool) IntegerType(bits) - Signed integers (i8, i16, i32, i64) UIntegerType(bits) - Unsigned integers (ui8, ui16, ui32, ui64) FloatType(bits) - Floating point (f32, f64) Utility functions: as_dtype(x): Convert string (e.g. \"f32\") DataType DataType object. is_dtype(x): Check whether object DataType. assert_dtype(x): Assert object DataType. Data types support equality comparison == !=.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/BooleanType.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"BooleanType — BooleanType","title":"BooleanType — BooleanType","text":"Represents boolean type.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/BooleanType.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"BooleanType — BooleanType","text":"","code":"BooleanType()"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/BooleanType.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"BooleanType — BooleanType","text":"BooleanType","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/DataType.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"DataType Base Class — DataType","title":"DataType Base Class — DataType","text":"DataType parent S3 class tensor data types. data type classes inherit DataType, enabling cross-type comparisons == != operators. specific data type classes : BooleanType() - Boolean (i1) IntegerType() - Signed integers (i8, i16, i32, i64) UIntegerType() - Unsigned integers (ui8, ui16, ui32, ui64) FloatType() - Floating point (f32, f64)","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/DataType.html","id":"details","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Details","title":"DataType Base Class — DataType","text":"virtual base class - create instances directly. Use specific type constructors instead.","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/FloatType.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"FloatType — FloatType","title":"FloatType — FloatType","text":"Represents floating point type given bit width.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/FloatType.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"FloatType — FloatType","text":"","code":"FloatType(value)"},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/FloatType.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"FloatType — FloatType","text":"value (integer(1))","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/FloatType.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"FloatType — FloatType","text":"FloatType","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/IntegerType.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"IntegerType (signed) — IntegerType","title":"IntegerType (signed) — IntegerType","text":"Represents signed integer type given bit width.","code":""},{"path":"https://r-xla.github.io/tengen/reference/IntegerT